<p>
  Of all the couple apps, <strong>Cozy Couples</strong> and <strong>OurCouple</strong> are the most alike — both turn your relationship into a warm, gamified space for two, complete with a virtual pet. Cozy leans into a decoratable virtual home; OurCouple leans into daily rituals, memories and privacy. Here's the honest comparison.
</p>

<h2>The Short Version</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Cozy Couples</strong> is a cozy, gamified space: a shared virtual home you decorate together (a bonsai tree, a virtual cat or dog, stars you earn and spend), real-time mood sharing, daily questions, games, love notes, countdowns, and a daily streak. It's free, and very well rated.</li>
  <li><strong>OurCouple</strong> is an all-in-one private space: a daily message + photo of the day, daily questions, a shared memory journal, love notes, a calendar, couple games with a <strong>compatibility score</strong>, and a virtual pet you raise together — end-to-end encrypted, with one subscription for both partners.</li>
</ul>

<p>
  <strong>Short answer:</strong> if you want the coziest free virtual home to decorate together, Cozy Couples is delightful. If you want that same warmth built around a daily ritual, a real memory journal, compatibility games and end-to-end encryption, OurCouple is the better fit.
</p>

