<h2>Pricing</h2>

<p>
  Cozy Couples is free. OurCouple is freemium — a generous free tier, with one premium subscription that covers both partners. If free-forever is your top priority, Cozy is a great choice. If you want the daily-ritual + memory-journal + privacy combination, OurCouple's free tier already covers a lot, and premium is shared rather than per-person.
</p>

<h2>Privacy</h2>

<p>
  OurCouple encrypts your shared content end-to-end. Cozy Couples does not advertise end-to-end encryption. Both are private spaces for two, but if you want your messages and memories technically locked to just the two of you, that's the difference — see <a href="/blog/relationship-data-encryption">why your relationship data deserves encryption</a>.
</p>

<h2>Who Each App Is For</h2>

<h3>Choose Cozy Couples if…</h3>
<ul>
  <li>You love the idea of decorating a shared virtual home together</li>
  <li>You want it completely free</li>
  <li>Mood sharing and a cozy pet are the features you're most excited about</li>
</ul>

<h3>Choose OurCouple if…</h3>
<ul>
  <li>You want a daily message + photo ritual at the center of the app</li>
  <li>You want a real, organized memory journal of your story</li>
  <li>You want couple games with a compatibility score that grows over time</li>
  <li>You care about end-to-end encryption and one subscription for both</li>
</ul>

